Write a program to check whether a given number n is a Perfect Number or not.

A Perfect Number is a number that is equal to the sum of all its proper divisors (factors excluding the number itself).

For example:

Factors of 6 are 1, 2, 3, 6

Proper divisors (excluding 6) = 1 + 2 + 3 = 6 ✅ Since the sum equals the number, 6 is a Perfect Number.

Input Format

A single integer n representing the number.

Constraints

1 ≤ n ≤ 10^6

Output Format

Perfect Number → if the number is perfect Not a Perfect Number → otherwise

Sample Input 0

6
Sample Output 0

Perfect Number
Sample Input 1

10
Sample Output 1

Not a Perfect Number

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#include <stdio.h>
#include <string.h>
#include <math.h>
#include <stdlib.h>

int main() {

    int n,sum=0;
    scanf("%d",&n)  ;
    for(int i=1;i<n;i++){
        if(n%i==0){
            sum+=i;
        }
    }
    if(sum==n){
        printf("Perfect Number");
    }
    else {
        printf("Not a Perfect Number");
    }
    return 0;
}
